(null, 'billiards-table-plus', 'Billiards Table Plus Game-Room Items', 'general-merchandise', 'unmanifested', 'customer-return', 310, 310, 1, 310, 'in-stock', array['/images/savemore/billiards-table-plus-1.webp'], 'This is a single unmanifested customer-return lot built around a pool table with additional game-room items and accessories sold as-is. Contents and condition vary, so plan to inspect rails, felt, pockets, and any included cues or balls before listing. The natural buyer is a local game-room, bar, or rec-space shopper sourced through Facebook Marketplace, Craigslist, or OfferUp, where high-ticket fixtures clear faster with photos and pickup terms. At $310 for the lot, it works as a one-piece flip rather than a unit play, so the margin is in negotiation and presentation. Stage it in a clean spot for photos and offer dock pickup or local delivery as a paid add-on.', 270),
(null, 'gaylord-liquidation-pallet', 'Gaylord Pallet, Bulk Mixed Merchandise', 'general-merchandise', 'unmanifested', 'customer-return', 340, 340, 1, 340, 'in-stock', array['/images/savemore/gaylord-liquidation-pallet-1.webp'], 'This gaylord-size container holds unmanifested customer-return and overstock merchandise packed deep with small-to-medium items across home, accessories, and general goods. Condition is mixed, so expect a working sort into resale, repair, and scrap rather than a clean shelf-ready load. The buyer profile here is a bin-store operator, flea-market vendor, or volume eBay reseller who profits on piece count rather than per-item retail. Priced at $340 for the full gaylord, the math depends on how many sellable units come out after sort. On intake, tip and sort by category into totes first, then grade for condition so the bin-store pricing tiers stay clean. Schedule a forklift-capable dock pickup.', 271),
(null, 'bj-s-smalls-hpc', 'BJ''s Smalls High-Piece-Count Pallet', 'general-merchandise', 'unmanifested', 'customer-return', 385, 385, 1, 385, 'in-stock', array['/images/savemore/bj-s-smalls-hpc-1.webp'], 'This is a high-piece-count pallet of small-format customer-return and overstock merchandise pulled from BJ''s Wholesale Club, mixing general goods, health and beauty, and household smalls. Manifest is not provided, so unit counts and category ratios vary load to load. It is built for bin-store operators and weekend flea-market sellers who price by the each across $1, $3, and $5 tiers, where small footprints and dense piece counts drive throughput. At $385 for the pallet, the play is volume recovery rather than hero items. On intake, run a fast triage into sellable, test-required, and scrap bins, then refill bins on a weekly cycle. Forklift pickup at the Jacksonville dock is available.', 272),
